ER  -
TY  - JOUR
AB  - Electronic cigarettes are a novel and emerging product increasingly used
      by the general public. However, despite their popularity, they remain
      poorly studied and with likely serious health risks. EVALI, or "electronic
      cigarette or vaping product use-associated lung injury," is a recently
      described entity at the forefront of current investigations. Though EVALI
      has been linked to vitamin E acetate, a constituent of THC vaping
      products, electronic cigarettes likely pose a host of other pulmonary
      toxicities. The presentation, diagnostic work-up, treatment, and
      pathophysiology of EVALI are herein described, as well as the general
      pulmonary toxicity profile of electronic cigarettes.
