AB  - The acute respiratory distress syndrome (ARDS) remains a major cause of
      morbidity and mortality in the intensive care unit. Improving outcomes
      depends on not only evidence-based care once ARDS has already developed
      but also preventing ARDS incidence. Several environmental exposures have
      now been shown to increase the risk of ARDS and related adverse outcomes.
      How environmental factors impact the risk of developing ARDS is a growing
      and important field of research that should inform the care of individual
      patients as well as public health policy.
